Defendant Nigel A Epps in court with attorney Michael G. Levine.  Patricia Irene Daugherty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. State placed negotiations on the record. PSI reviewed by the parties. Court finds the state has complied with the victim rights legislation. Statements made as to sentencing. Additional statements made by Alicia M.

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 84 MONTHS, with credit for 10 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 48 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 36 MONTHS.  

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 4 YEARS with the following conditions:
1) Court ordered 1 YEAR of condition time in the House of Correction. Defendant to report to the House of Correction on 12/04/15 by 10:00 a.m. Defendant may have release for work with proof of employment. If the defendant is not employed, he is eligible for the Day Reporting Center with participation in vocational/educational programming. Defendant may have release for school with proof of enrollment.;
2) Pay all costs, fees, surcharges, and resitution during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
3) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
4) Pay restitution in the amount of $317.00 payable to Walgreens Corporation; 
5) No contact with the victim Dina S. or the Walgreens at 2950 N. Oakland Avenue. Defendant may have contact with the victim for purposes of Restorative Justice if approved by the victim;
6) Commit no new crimes;
7) Maintain absolute sobriety;
8) AODA assessment and comply with recommended treatment;
9) Attend parenting class;
10) Provide prescriptions to agent before filling the prescription;

Defendant to enter into a payment plan with the agent.

If revoked, court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of wages/earnings.

If revoked, defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
